{"id":725,"date":"2022-11-13T16:32:00","date_gmt":"2022-11-13T14:32:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=725"},"modified":"2022-12-09T19:28:26","modified_gmt":"2022-12-09T17:28:26","slug":"send-money-abroad-what-you-need-to-know","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/send-money-abroad-what-you-need-to-know\/","title":{"rendered":"\ud83d\udca1 Sending Money Abroad: All You Need to Know"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Individuals commonly send money abroad for different purposes, e.g., remitting money to family or paying employees in a different country. If you\u2019re an ex-pat, you may want to do this when buying a car or a house in your new country of residence.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.consumerfinance.gov\/consumer-tools\/sending-money\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Consumer Financial Protection Bureau<\/a>, you should know a few things before using banking as a service platform to remit money. These will include your rights, the information the platform should provide, and how to compare costs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from your rights, there\u2019s a need to learn about the different platforms available and how each operates. Most importantly, you should know that remitting funds internationally depends on whether you want to value, security, speed, or a blend of all three.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"item-673d660a4a473\" aria-label=\"Table of Content\"><span style=\"display: flex;align-items: center;width: 35px;height: 30px;justify-content: center;direction:ltr;\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=